      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "CHEAP REALITY (4) rocketed out of the inside draw with a strong early sectional and gave a sight but had to settle for a placing, finishing second (24.14) at Rockhampton over 407m. The form from her last run is stacking up nicely. Leading chance again. RINGWALD (1) had a tricky draw last time and although midfield in fifth wasn't far away finishing 3.5 lengths from the winner (22.01). Has a good record here at this journey. Worth another chance. FEDERAL BLAST (3) is a quick dog who thrives over the short dashes. Found it a bit far latest when finished eighth over 498m at this track (30.15) in a Grade 5/6 but is better suited back in trip here. Form here at this distance is sound including six wins. Has the ability to give this a shake. WHITE CAR (2) placed at long odds last time and cannot be ignored.",
